We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Among the options listed, Intrauterine device (IUD) is the most efficacious method of contraception, with a failure rate of less than 1% per year. NuvaRing is also a good option with a failure rate of 1-2% per year, but it requires the patient to remember to insert and remove it. Male condoms and diaphragm with spermicide have higher failure rates and are not as effective as IUDs and NuvaRing.
